        "author": {
          "name": "Sebastien Buisson",
          "email": "sbuisson@ddn.com",
          "date": "2019-11-06 17:31:08.000000000",
          "tz": 540
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2020-01-03 23:44:00.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-12944 mdd: pass correct xattr size to lower layers",
        "message": "LU-12944 mdd: pass correct xattr size to lower layers\n\nIn mdd_iterate_xattrs(), struct lu_buf allocated to store xattr value\ncan be reused for multiple xattrs, because it is only reallocated if\nit happens to be too small for one xattr.\nAs a consequence, lb_len field does not represent actual xattr's size.\nIt has to be adjusted when passed to lower layers.\n\nLustre-change: https://review.whamcloud.com/36689\nLustre-commit: e5e584fd386a2229809bc64d440c3255cf50c1bd\n\nSigned-off-by: Sebastien Buisson <sbuisson@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: I26b54759b4e69fbac17a1032bbc724b796d78108\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/37030\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_12"
    }
  },
